    "problemStatement": "You are given two integers NNN and MMM.\n\nFind the sum of (\u2211i=1N\u2223Ai\u2212Bi\u2223)2(\\sum_{i=1}^{N} |A_i-B_i|)^2(\u2211i=1N\u200b\u2223Ai\u200b\u2212Bi\u200b\u2223)2, over all pairs of arrays AAA and BBB such that\n\n\nAAA and BBB consists of NNN elements\nAiA_iAi\u200b and BiB_iBi\u200b are integers, where 0\u2264Ai,Bi\u2264M0 \\leq A_i, B_i \\leq M0\u2264Ai\u200b,Bi\u200b\u2264M\n\u2211i=1NAi=\u2211i=1NBi=M\\sum_{i=1}^{N}A_i=\\sum_{i=1}^{N}B_i=M\u2211i=1N\u200bAi\u200b=\u2211i=1N\u200bBi\u200b=M\nSince the sum might be large, please print it modulo 998244353998244353998244353.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line of input contains a single integer TTT, denoting the number of test cases.\nThe only line of each test case contains two positive integers NNN and MMM, the number of elements of AAA and the sum of elements of AAA respectively.\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output on a new line the required sum modulo 998244353998244353998244353.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u22641031 \\leq T \\leq 10^31\u2264T\u2264103",
      "1\u2264N\u22645\u22c51021 \\leq N \\leq 5 \\cdot 10^21\u2264N\u22645\u22c5102",
      "1\u2264M\u22641051 \\leq M \\leq 10^51\u2264M\u2264105",
      "The sum of MMM over all test cases won't exceed 10510^5105."
    ],
